<topic xml:lang="en-US" id="d0e122"><title>Using The Priorities</title><body><p>Once you've created priorities they can be used anywhere you would normally choose books. For instance,</p><ul><li>Find dialog (Ctrl+F)</li><li>Click on <b>Choose</b></li><li>Select the <b>Priority</b> tab.</li></ul><p><image href="../PT9.1%20video%20summaries%20EN_files/image5.png" height="134" width="335" alt="???"/></p><ul><li>Assignments [XMLmind] Progress (blue button), book selection can be set to a priority.</li></ul><p><image href="../PT9.1%20video%20summaries%20EN_files/image6.png" height="107" width="265" alt="???"/></p><ul><li>(Project menu) Export PDF, click Choose </li></ul><p><image href="../PT9.1%20video%20summaries%20EN_files/image7.png" height="148" width="284" alt="???"/></p><ul><li>Any window with a filter</li></ul><p><image href="../PT9.1%20video%20summaries%20EN_files/image8.png" height="140" width="302" alt="???"/></p><p>You can also define or redefine my priorities if you need to.</p></body></topic>